OL,3,CLab-grown coral could save the vibrant
OL,4,Cocean landscape
OL,6,FIt is estimated that by 2030 around
OL,7,F90% of reefs could be extinct.
OL,9,FNaturally, corals only reproduce once
OL,10,Fa year. This is dependent on the lunar
OL,11,Fcycle, and water temperature.
OL,13,FAll mature corals will release their
OL,14,Feggs and sperm, at the same time
OL,15,Fmeaning it is more likely that
OL,16,Ffertilisation will occur.
OL,18,FDays after being fertilised and
OL,19,Ffloating in the water, embryos called
OL,20,Fplanula will fall to the ocean floor
OL,21,Fwhere they will settle for life.
